column1: Man, what's the deal with this place?

Indeed. We never expected a birdcage to
collapse with the defeat of a warden.
It could be due to the lack of a Monarch.
Whatever the case is, the Desires should've been released back to their owners. The locals should all be back to normal by now.

I seriously hope so—I don't feel like living
through another B-movie...

After all your efforts, this mission was fruitless.
I'm sorry you had to endure that because of
me.
I admit, it was a bummer...

He's right. Plus, I'm sure you'll find out who
you are eventually.

True, but I'm sure we'll find out what we need
if we keep infiltrating Jails.
However, I did at least figure out one thing.
When the voice called me worthless, I was sad.

But when that made everyone angry, I became
happy.

I still feel that way—even now, there is a
warmth within me...
I have friends. I know I'm not alone.
Thank you, Joker. Thank you, Skull, Mona.

R-Really? You just figured that out now? I
mean, that thing just really pissed me off,
is all...

Yeah, and I was just trying to reel in Skull,
so, uh...

Oho, what's this? Two embarrassed Phantom
Thieves?
Even your masks are glowing red.
How's my mask suppose'ta change color!?
Mona's black mask makes it difficult to tell.
Well, we should head back to the exit.
I feel like I'm gonna pass out.
Mmhm, I bet he's weeping like a baby by now!
Yes, we should go check on them.
Tell me about it... I'm about to pass out myself.

I can feel a strong
bond with my friends...
